d Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":37,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705195,"age":82,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Margery Headon was born after 1299, in England as the daughter of Thomas Headon. She married Sir Adam De Hopton in 1349. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"after 1299–":"pärast 1299–Surnud","1299–Female":"1299–Surnud","1299–Male":"1299–Surnud","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1453":"1453","1299":"1299","1275":"1275","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","after 1299":"pärast 1299","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"after 1299–":"1299 jälkeen–Kuollut","1299–Female":"1299–Kuollut","1299–Male":"1299–Kuollut","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1453":"1453","1299":"1299","1275":"1275","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","after 1299":"1299 jälkeen","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"after 1299–":"après 1299–Décédée","1299–Female":"1299–Décédée","1299–Mal